<item>
            <title>[LANG-1668] Unlisted breaking change in behaviour of MethodUtils#getMatchingMethod</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LANG-1668</link>
                <project id="12310481" key="LANG">Commons Lang</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;After upgrading from 3.11 to 3.12 some Unit Tests of mine were failing.&lt;br/&gt;
I tracked this back to an undocumented change in lang3:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;MethodUtils#getMatchingMethod is behaving differently.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Previously, it returned the closest match when no exact match could be found.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Now, it throws an&#160;IllegalStateException when there is no unique result.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It would have saved me some time if this had been noted in the change notes.&lt;br/&gt;
Not quite sure where to bring this up or whether this qualifies as a bug, but I hope I&apos;m helping by mentioning it here.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
